Dear Rubitherm Team,

I hope you’re thriving as this note comes your way,

We at EAF, a private organization established at the request of the Brazilian National Telecommunications Agency (ANATEL) to support the deployment of 5G technology in Brazil, are currently developing an off-grid energy and amplification station intended for operation in the Amazon rainforest. This autonomous station is powered by three 500 W solar panels and includes and includes a sealed container (approximately 4 ft in size) housing an optical amplifier (EDFA) and a solar controller. The thermal management system combines polyurethane insulation and phase change materials (PCMs).
We have selected RT22HC as the PCM candidate due to its suitable phase transition temperature (22 °C) and its paraffin-based formulation.

Application Details:

  *   Thermal insulation: 2 cm of polyurethane foam applied via internal wall spray;
  *   PCM: 2 cm layer, encapsulated in aluminum/PE panels;
  *   Fixation: PCM panels are mechanically fixed over the PU using aluminum support structures;
  *   Thermal load: Approx. 33 W internal (EDFA + controller);
  *   External temperature: ~38 °C during peak hours;
  *   Target internal temperature: ~22 °C;
  *   Estimated PCM requirement: 39 kg (~0.051 m³).

We kindly request:

  1.  A quotation for the supply of RT22HC, including packaging and delivery options;
  2.  Technical recommendations for long-term encapsulation and mounting of RT22HC inside sealed enclosures;
  3.  Estimated lead times and availability for export to Brazil.

We look forward to your response and are available to provide further details if needed.
Best regards,
Decilio Sales
EAF – Technical Consultant
